COM S 327 Programming Project 1.10/2
Choose Your Own Assignment - Pokemon Game Extension

This submission extends the Pokemon game from Assignment 1.09 with extra battle,
item, money, catching, and Pokemon Center mechanics.

Implemented features:

1. PokeBucks money system
   - The PC now has a money field called pokebucks.
   - The player starts with 500 PokeBucks.
   - Money is spent at PokeMarts and earned by defeating trainers.

2. Trainer money rewards
   - When the player defeats a trainer, that trainer is marked defeated.
   - The trainer drops a random amount of PokeBucks based on the size of the
     trainer's Pokemon party.
   - The battle message tells the player how many PokeBucks were earned.

3. PokeMart shopping
   - PokeMarts no longer refill supplies for free.
   - Press '>' while standing on a PokeMart to open the shop.
   - Potions, Revives, and Pokeballs each cost 100 PokeBucks.
   - The shop shows the player's current money and item counts.

4. Improved Pokemon catching
   - Pokeballs no longer catch wild Pokemon every time.
   - Catch chance is based on a simplified formula using the wild Pokemon's
     remaining HP and level.
   - Lower HP makes a Pokemon easier to catch.
   - Higher level Pokemon are harder to catch.

5. Pokemon Center storage and party management
   - If the player's party is full and a wild Pokemon is caught, the new Pokemon
     is sent to Pokemon Center storage instead of fleeing.
   - Press '>' while standing on a Pokemon Center to heal and open the center
     menu.
   - Press 'S' in the Pokemon Center to manage party/storage.
   - Deposit party Pokemon with keys 1-6.
   - Withdraw stored Pokemon with keys a-j.
   - The player must always keep at least one Pokemon in the active party.

6. Type effectiveness in battle damage
   - Damage now uses a type effectiveness multiplier.
   - Dual-typed defending Pokemon multiply both type effectiveness values.
   - Battle messages report whether moves are super effective, not very
     effective, or have no effect.

Other battle controls from the previous assignment are still supported:

- Fight: choose a Pokemon move.
- Bag: use Potion, Revive, or Pokeball during battle.
- Run: flee from wild battles only.
- Pokemon: switch active Pokemon.
- B: open the bag outside of battle.
- Q: quit the game.

Files changed for this extension:

- character.h
- pokemon.h
- pokemon.cpp
- io.cpp
- README
- Changelog
